sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Route as TrustyAI Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Reencrypt
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as PVC or Database<br/>Filesystem or 5432/3306 TCP

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 1: External User Access

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.3
    Router->>Route: Route to Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Route->>OAuth: Forward Request<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Service Serving Cert
    OAuth->>OAuthServer: Validate Token<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>OAuth Client
    OAuthServer-->>OAuth: Token Valid
    OAuth->>TrustyAI: Proxied Request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (localhost)<br/>OAuth Token Validated
    TrustyAI-->>OAuth: Response
    OAuth-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 2: Inference Data Collection from KServe

    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService

    KServe->>TrustyAI: POST Inference Payload<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+ (Service Serving Cert)<br/>mTLS
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Store Data<br/>Filesystem or PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>None or TLS 1.2+<br/>Filesystem or DB Credentials
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Acknowledged
    TrustyAI-->>KServe: 200 OK

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 3: Metrics Scraping

    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Prom->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP<br/>None (internal)
    TrustyAI-->>Prom: Prometheus Metrics<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)

    Note over User,Storage: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation

    participant Operator as Operator Controller
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch TrustyAIService CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: CR Event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, Routes, etc.)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resource Created
